data.name: lblInstructions.Text
data.value: This How-To demonstrates the creation and installation of a Windows Service. To do this it depends on the three different projects. The first project ("C#.NET How-To Creating a Windows Service") provides a UI for the demo and verifies if the service is currently installed. The second project ("C#.NET How-To Windows Service Demo") is the actual code that creates the Windows Service. Finally, the third project ("C#.NET How-To Windows Service - Time Track Install") is used to demonstrate the creation of an install package for a Windows Service. For more information, please see the included ReadMe.htm file.

data.name: lblInstallationStatus.Text
data.value: WARNING: The Service has not been installed! Use the "C#.NET How-To Windows Service - Time Track.msi" to install it. That file can be found in the root directory of this How To. Once installed, press the Verify Install button.
